l,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EMast cells express high-affinity receptors (Fc\u03b5RI) that specifically bind to \u003Cstrong\u003EIgE\u003C/strong\u003E antibodies. When allergens cross-link these surface-bound IgE molecules, it triggers mast cell degranulation. Neither \u003Cstrong\u003EIgA\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003EIgG\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003EIgD\u003C/strong\u003E, nor \u003Cstrong\u003EIgM\u003C/strong\u003E can trigger this response.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EDuring degranulation, mast cells release preformed mediators including histamine, proteases, and heparin, as well as newly synthesized mediators like prostaglandins and leukotrienes. These substances produce the characteristic symptoms of immediate hypersensitivity reactions such as vasodilation, increased vascular permeability, and smooth muscle contraction.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Immunoglobulin E (IgE) antibodies bound to mast cell surface receptors trigger degranulation when cross-linked by allergens.","Mast cell degranulation releases histamine and other inflammatory mediators responsible for allergic responses."],"references":["Tigner A, Ibrahim SA, Murray IV. Histology, White Blood Cell. [Updated 2022 Nov 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK563148/","Janeway CA Jr, Travers P, Walport M, et al. Immunobiology: The Immune System in Health and Disease. 5th edition. New York: Garland Science; 2001. The production of IgE. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK27117/","Playfair, J. H. L., \u0026 Chain, B. M. (2012). Immunology at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44549"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14877"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44549","links":{"self":"h